title: Bending energy
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The //bending energy// of a parametrized curve $$\gamma\colon [0,L] \to \R^2$$ is given by
$$
E(\gamma) \coloneqq \int_0^L \kappa^2 \,\d s,
$$
where $$\d s = v \,\d x.$$ If $$\gamma_0\colon [0,L]$$ is arc length parametrized and $$\gamma$$ is a varation, then
$$
\dot E =
-2\kappa \lang \dot\gamma',N \rang \big|_0^L +
\lang \dot\gamma, 2\kappa'N-\kappa^2T \rang \big|_0^L -
\int_0^L (2\kappa''+ \kappa^3)\lang \dot\gamma,N \rang \,\d s.
$$